    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KAC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Presidents Special Assistant</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_HHL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Temporarily at Tehran</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d346fn1">Sent via Army channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-29">November 29,
                            1943.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With reference to my message of yesterday Chinese Chargé<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d346fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_TaW1">T’ang Wu</persName>.</note> has just called to
                    say that he has cabled text of document to Chungking with instructions to hold
                    release pending flash from him.</p>
                <p>I told him that I had been instructed to notify him when I received word from
                    Tehran of date of release. As matters now stand therefore texts of document in
                    question are in Foreign Offices in London and Chungking, but unless you have
                    sent text direct there is none in Washington. Do you wish me to cable text in
                    advance to State Department to be held pending instructions as to date of
                    release or are you taking action in Tehran?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KAC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
